esearch enterprise at University of Illinois and reduce the administrative burden for faculty and business office staff, ultimately saving the University money and ensuring that we are fulfilling our financial, legal, and ethical obligations.         MyResearch Portal         MyResearch Portal    myResearch integrates and displays information from a number of different university systems, giving faculty access to the information they need to prepare, submit, route, and manage their grants.  myResearch Portal can be used by PI’s and Business Managers  MyResearch Portal Updates         myProposals         myProposals   myProposals – Prepare and submit proposals for central office review and approval        START myDisclosures         START myDisclosures   START myDisclosures is the online application to perform the following processes for compliance with the University Policy on Conflict of Commitment and Interest :   Academic Staff submit the Report of Non-University Activities (RNUA)  Unit Executive Officers review and manage RNUA disclosures  Investigators submit the Sponsor Specific – Significant Financial Interest disclosures  Investigators manage Sponsor Specific Financial Conflicts of Interest (FCOI)  Unit Executive Officers review Sponsor Specific FCOI Management Plans  Investigators or business managers submit FCOI Checklists (coming in winter 2016/spring 2017)  Investigator or business mangers track investigator FCOI training (coming in winter 2016/spring 2017)         OPRS Live         OPRS Live    OPRS Live is a web-based, IRB submission system that allows PI’s and their staff to create and submit online IRB applications including electronic routing for signatures.         OSPWeb         OSPWeb    OSPWeb is the web-based system used to deliver documents to OSP.  OSPWeb eliminates the need to submit hard copies of all documents to our front office.  OSPWeb sends emails confirming receipt of delivery and assignment to OSP personnel for review.               